Package com.github.actionfx.core.beans

Class BeanProperty<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.actionfx.core.beans.BeanProperty<T>
  • public class BeanProperty<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    A specific property inside a Java bean. This class holds routines to access the value via regular getter, property-getter or direct field access.

    Constructing this instance is (comparably) expensive, because it uses reflection to lookup getter, setter and field. Instances of this class should be therefore cached.

    Author:
    koster

      • getValue

        public T getValue​(java.lang.Object bean)
        Gets the value from the supplied bean.

        In case, the property is indexed, the indexed value is returned.

        In case the property is mapped, the value under the map key is retrieved.

        In case it is a non-indexed, non-mapped property, the value is retrieved either via the regular getter or via the property-getter, in case the getter is not available. In case the property-getter is also not available, direct field access for getting the value is attempted.

        Parameters:
        bean - the bean holding the property value
        Returns:
        the property value
